        <h2>Apple cider vinegar</h2>
        <div class="xyz">
            <div class="pqr">
        <p>Our hair's natural pH is on the acidic side, and an imbalance where it bends more towards the alkaline side can often cause frizziness.
             Apple cider vinegar, an alpha hydroxy acid, can restore that balance and help you get rid of that frizz. </p>
        <p>How to apply this?</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Mix a litre of warm water with 1/3 cup of apple cider vinegar.</li> 
            <li>Pour this over your hair and keep it on for a few minutes.</li>
            <li>Rinse and air dry your hair.</li>
        </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="pqr">
        <img src="https://post.healthline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/apple-cider-vinegar-732x549-thumbnail-1-732x549.jpg">
